    <section class="section section--manray" ng-show="page === 'manray'">
        <p>The Dada artist Man Ray, who is Lily’s great-granduncle, has served as a tremendous source of artistic inspiration for both Lily and Adal.</p>
        <p>In June 2011, Lily decided she wanted to get a tattoo of Man Ray’s <i>Calla Lillies</i>, and she chose Adal as her tattoo artist after he was recommended by a mutual friend. Adal was no stranger to the works of Man Ray and the Dada and surrealist movements - he had even given his son the middle name “Dali.” From an early age, Adal had gravitated towards the disposition of the Dada manifestos and notions of anti-art inevitably creating art, drawing inspiration from Rayographs, and the glowing qualities of Man Ray’s “solarized” prints.</p>
        <p>In honor of Man Ray, and in an effort to continue his legacy and chosen name through bloodline, the couple will assume the surname Ray through this marital union.</p>
    </section>
